==English==

===Adjective===
'''mad''' ({{compar}} '''madder''', {{superl}} '''maddest''')

# [[Insane]].
#:''You want to spend $1000 on a pair of shoes?  Are you mad?''
#:''He's got this mad idea that he's irresistible to women.''
# Arranged or designed in a insane way.
#:''The room was mad''.
# (''especially US'') [[Angry]].
#:''Are you mad at me?''
# Cheap.
#:''They have the maddest prices.''
# (''colloquial''; ''followed by'' '''for''') [[Want]]ing intensely.
#:''Aren't you just mad for that red dress?''

===Noun===
'''mad'''
# {{rfv-sense}} Leader of Hostile Takeover

===Adverb===
'''mad'''

# {{colloquial}} A general-purpose intensifier: [[very]], [[unbelievable|unbelievably]]
#:''He was driving mad slow''

